com: DS9 is an overrated star trek. It's still one of my favourites because it got me into star trek but on rewatch it's problems come out full force. Mainly because the writers had no idea what the hell they wanted to do from day one, knowing the ending for your story and why you're writing it in the first place is important. The series introduces elements to retroactively fix the writing in earlier seasons which creates new problems. The most glaring example is Julian Bashir who the writers had no idea what to do with him earlier on but then said he was a genetically engineered test-tube baby which introduces the retarded autism club subplot that goes nowhere and cheapens his character. Jadzia Dax is another really bad example of how the writers didn't have a clue to the story they wanted to tell, it takes about 3 seasons to "fix" her non-existent character and then she's killed off and replaced by another actress for Ezri Dax that still doesn't fix the problem about 6 seasons in. The writer spergout when Gul Dukat got too popular with fans because the actor understood and played his character perfectly. Kira Nerys would take about a page to summarise her problems, Odo is all over the fucking place, Jake goes nowhere. Quark, Dukat, and Garak are about the only good stand-out characters in this character driven show which is pretty bad. Not to mention all the retarded and terrible subplots like the Ferengi one or poorly executed episodes like any Dax one. Worf is retroactively ruined to make DRAMA with his son. This show is just all over the place and if you listen to the behind the scenes stuff you can really tell.
